HEADWORD: Anamorphism
<hw>An`a*mor"phism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
again + <grk>morfh`</grk> form.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A distorted
image.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A gradual progression from one
type to another, generally ascending.</def>
<rj><au>Huxley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anamorphoscope</ent>⟦br⟧
